                        Ambassador in China (
                        Stuart
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d670</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">670</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-01-16T16:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-01-16T16:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="670" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d670">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">846G.79693/1–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-16T16:00:00-05:00">January 16, 1948—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Shanghai’s tel 78, Jan 15 to you<note n="16" xml:id="d670fn16">Sent to the
                        Department as telegram No. 102, <ref target="#pg_779">p. 779</ref>.</note>
                    confirms info given Dept by PAA. Dept views this Chinese projected unilateral
                    action with grave concern and approves Emb representations. Dept awaits further
                    details with interest.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking as 67; rptd Shanghai as 80.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
